# =====================================================================================
# RPE-1 human cell-cycle regulatory network -- rule-based ODE model, edition-2 PyBNF fit
# to single-cell trajectory data.  This is the paper's headline PARAMETER-FITTING problem
# (177 of 205 parameters estimated), NOT the Fig-1 transition submodels.
#
# Real-world PyBNF edition-2 fitting job derived from:
#   Lang PF, Penas DR, Banga JR, Weindl D, Novak B. "Reusable rule-based cell cycle model
#   explains compartment-resolved dynamics of 16 observables in RPE-1 cells."
#   PLoS Comput Biol 2024; 20(1):e1011151.  DOI 10.1371/journal.pcbi.1011151.
#
# Model + PEtab problem: paulflang/cell_cycle_petab @ versions/v3.2.0 (commit d562d3d),
#   a manual BNGL translation of the authors' SBML model (cell_cycle_v3.2.0.bngl).  The
#   PEtab problem (parameters/observables/experimentalCondition TSVs + v3.2.0.yaml) was
#   transcribed into this native edition-2 job by the curate-pybnf-job skill.
#
# Fit target -- 8 NUCLEAR observables over ~2 cell cycles (single-cell RPE-1 median
#   trajectories, Stallaert et al., Cell Systems 2021; the data were duplicated to two
#   cycles to enforce sustained oscillation, per the paper's Text F):
#     obs_cycA/cycB1/cycE/E2F1/pRB/Skp2/p21/p27 __nuc_median()  (model functions -> parens
#     in the .exp header).  Each observable is offset + scale*sum-of-species; the 8 offsets
#     (o*) and 8 scales (s*) are fitted observation-model parameters (see below).
#
# HAS begin compartments (cell) -> ODE only; NFsim is out.  The network is finite (73
#   species, 332 reactions, builds in ~0.3 s), but the FIT is cluster-scale (177 free
#   params, single wt condition, 600 time points) -> the manifest marks it heavy=True.
#
# Adaptations from the staged model (edition-2, fitting-ready):
#   * simulation actions (generate_network/writeSBML/simulate) stripped -- synthesized
#     from v3_2_0.conf; the bare default generate_network is correct (finite network).
#   * kinetic rate constants declared as bare `id value` (exact SBML values), bound by
#     name to the .conf free params (ADR-0034, no __FREE alias).
#   * every seed species carries an ic_wt_cell__<flat> initial-concentration parameter --
#     the wt PEtab condition.  BNG's canonical species order matches the PEtab/SBML species
#     order 1:1, so these names are the PEtab initial-concentration parameter ids verbatim.
#     NB: species 60-73 (CDKN1A/CDKN1B monomers + cyclin:CKI complexes) were GENERATED at
#     init 0 in the staged model but the PEtab problem fits them nonzero initials, so they
#     are seeded explicitly here.
#   * observation model added as functions obs_*__nuc_median() = o* + s*<sum> over the
#     Species observables below (total cyclin/CKI/Skp2 = the molecule total; pRB = the free
#     phospho-RB species; E2F1 = total E2F minus the phospho-Ser332 promoter-bound forms).
#
# Run (with BNGPATH set, from this folder):
#   cd pybnf-jobs/Lang-2024/v3_2_0 && pybnf -c v3_2_0.conf
# =====================================================================================

begin model
